<div id="orders-help">
    <h2>Orders</h2>
    The orders selections are how you manage the orders you have recieved. Here you can do many things, such as creating an order,
    editing, deleting an order, and setting their status. This is the part of the TurkeyBase that you will be using the most. Each order
    is tied to an <a href="#order-season">order season</a>.
    <br/><br/>
    <div id="new-order">
        <h3>New Order</h3>
        <img src="/New_Order.png" />
        <dl>
            <dt>1. Order Season Name</dt>
            <dd>
                This is the name of the current active order season. The order will be placed into this order season.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>2. Customer First Name</dt>
            <dd>
                The first name of the customer on the order. This is a required field.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>3. Customer Last Name</dt>
            <dd>
                The last name of the customer on the order. This is a required field.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>4. Customer Phone Number</dt>
            <dd>
                The customer's phone number on the order. Use only the number for the phone (Eg. 9054761234 instead
                of (905)476-1234).This is a required field.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>5. Order Product</dt>
            <dd>
                The product that the customer is ordering. Dropdown menu with products that are in the active
                ordering season. This is a required field.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>6. Order Product Size</dt>
            <dd>
                The size of the product that the customer is ordering. The selectable objects are dependent on
                what product you have chosen. This is a required field.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>7. Order Product Style</dt>
            <dd>
                The style of the product that the customer is ordering. The selectable objects are dependent on
                what product you have chosen. This is a required field.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>8. Order Pickup Date</dt>
            <dd>
                The date that the order is to be picked up. A list of dates that are tied to the active ordering
                season. This is a required field.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>9. Special Requests</dt>
            <dd>
                This field is for any special requests that cannot be fill by selecting one of the styles in the dropdown
                menu.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>10. Employee</dt>
            <dd>
                The employee that is taking the order. This is populated by the sales employees. If your name is not on
                this list, please contact your manager who handles the administration of your TurkeyBase system. This
                field is required.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>11. Save Order</dt>
            <dd>
                Once you confirm your order with the customer, click this to save the order in the TurkeyBase. If anything
                isn't valid you will be notified of the errors before you can save it.
            </dd>
        </dl>
    </div>
    <br/><br/>
