    <div id="manage-orders">
        <h3>Manage Orders</h3>
        <img src="/Manage_Orders.png" />
        <dl>
            <dt>1. Order Season</dt>
            <dd>
                The order season to display the list of orders for. Defaults to the active season. Selecting another
                order season in the drop down menu will swap to that order season.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>2. Number of Orders to Show</dt>
            <dd>
                Select how many orders you would like to show at one time. Defaults to 10.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>3. Search for Orders</dt>
            <dd>
                Use this to search for orders. Any field is searchable.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>4. List of Orders</dt>
            <dd>
                A list of orders for the currently selected order season.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>5. Order Status</dt>
            <dd>
                The status of the order, can either be "picked up" or "ordered". If you click on the status, it will
                change to the other status.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>6. Special Request Notification</dt>
            <dd>
                Notification that only shows up on orders with a special request. If you hover over this you can see
                the request. You can also go into the edit screen for that order to view the special request.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>7. Edit Order</dt>
            <dd>
                Click this to be redirected to the <a href="#edit-order">edit order</a> screen.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>8. Running Totals: Total, Sizes, Styles</dt>
            <dd>
                A running total of the product. A list gets created for each product in the order season. Shows the total of that product
                order, and breaks it down by sizes & styles as well.
                <br/><br/>
            </dd>
            <dt>9. Running Totals: Dates</dt>
            <dd>
                A running total of the product order statuses. Shows how many have been ordered, picked up, and remaining for
                each day. A list gets created for each product in the order season.
            </dd>
        </dl>
    </div>
</div>
