    <div id="order-season">
        <h2>Order Seasons</h2>
        The order season is how you can track the orders on specific seasons, for example: Thanksgiving 2018. Only one season is active
        at a time, and orders are automatically placed in that active season. You have to select which <a href="#products">products</a>
        you would like in that season. Pickup dates are tied to your order season. If you delete an order season, all orders that are
        in that season will be lost.
        <br/><br/>
        <div id="new-season">
            <h3>New Order Season</h3>
            <img src="/New_Season.png" />
            <dl>
                <dt>1. Order Season Name</dt>
                <dd>
                    The name of the new order season. This field is required.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>2. Start & End Date for the Order Season</dt>
                <dd>
                    Date pickers for the start and end date for the order season. The TurkeyBase will create pickup dates for this
                    order season within the dates that you have selected. These fields are required.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>3. Active Ordering Season</dt>
                <dd>
                    Select this box to make your new season the active order season. This will make any currently active order
                    season become unactive.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>4. Save Order Season</dt>
                <dd>
                    Click this to save your order season. You must first have selected a start and end date.
                    You will be redirected to the <a href="#edit-season">edit order season</a> page once it saves
                    successfully.
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
        <br/><br/>
        <div id="edit-season">
            <h3>Edit Order Season</h3>
            <img src="/Edit_Season.png" />
            <dl>
                <dt>1. Order Season Name</dt>
                <dd>
                    The name of the order season.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>2. Active Ordering Season</dt>
                <dd>
                    Select this is make the season the active one. This will unselect the current active season automatically.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>3. Save Order Season</dt>
                <dd>
                    Saves the order season. You must first save your order season name and changes to the active order season
                    before you add a pickup date or a product, otherwise your changes will be lost.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>4. Show Pickup Date Picker</dt>
                <dd>
                    Shows the date picker to add a new pickup date.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>5. Pickup Date List</dt>
                <dd>
                    A list of pickup dates that are in the season. Deleting one will remove all orders with that pickup date.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>6. Product Dropdown</dt>
                <dd>
                    A dropdown list of all products that aren't currently in the order season. This menu shows when you click
                    the product equivalent of the #4 option on this menu.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>7. Add a Product</dt>
                <dd>
                    Add the selected product to the order season. This makes is so product is selectable in the order menu.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>8. Delete a Product From the Season</dt>
                <dd>
                    This removes a product from a season. This won't remove any orders that have selected that product
                    in the season. Deleting the product just makes the product non-selectable in the order menu.
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
        <br/><br/>
        <div id="manage-seasons">
            <h3>Manage Order Seasons</h3>
            <img src="/Manage_Seasons.png"/>
            <dl>
                <dt>1. Order Season</dt>
                <dd>
                    The name of an order season. Click this to edit the order season.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>2. Active Order Season</dt>
                <dd>
                    Denotes your current active order season.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>3. List of Order Seasons</dt>
                <dd>
                    A list of all your order seasons. The active season will automatically be at the top of the list.
                    Otherwise they are sorted alphabetically.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>4. Delete Order Season</dt>
                <dd>
                    This permanently deletes the order season. This will delete anything that is related to the order season.
                    <strong>THIS ACTION IS IRRIVERSABLE!</strong>
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
    </div>
