    <div id="products">
        <h2>Products</h2>
        Products as the products that are offered from your establishment. They get chosen by an <a href="#order-season">order season</a>
        to be able to be picked for an <a href="orders-help">order</a> within that season. If you delete a product, you will lose any
        orders that are related to that product.
        <div id="new-product">
            <h3>New Product</h3>
            <img src="/new_product.png" />
            <dl>
                <dt>1. Product Name</dt>
                <dd>
                    The name of the product that you are adding.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>2. Save Product</dt>
                <dd>
                    Click this to save your product. You must first have a size & style added in the
                    boxes below. You will be redirected to the <a href="#edit-product">edit product</a>
                    page once it saves successfully.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>3. Enable Size</dt>
                <dd>
                    Select this to have your size selectable in the drop down menu when placing an
                    order.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>4. Size Name</dt>
                <dd>
                    The name of the first size that you are adding to the product. This is a required field.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>5. Enable Style</dt>
                <dd>
                    Select this to have your style selectable in the drop down menu when placing an
                    order.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>6. Style Name</dt>
                <dd>
                    The name of the first style that you are adding to your product. This is a required field
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
        <br/><br/>
        <div id="edit-product">
            <h3>Edit Product</h3>
            <img src="/Edit_Product.png"></img>
            <dl>
                <dt>1. Product Name</dt>
                <dd>
                    The name of the product that you are editing.<br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>2. Update Product</dt>
                <dd>
                    When you click this button, it will update the product name.<br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>3. Enable New Product Size</dt>
                <dd>
                    Check this box to have a new size be enabled by default. This does the same thing
                    for style in its new style field.<br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>4. New Product Size Name</dt>
                <dd>
                    This is the name of the new size for your product. This is the same for adding a new style in
                    its new style field.<br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>5. Add New Product Size</dt>
                <dd>
                    Clicking this will add the new size to the product. You must first save your changes to the
                    product name if you have made any before you add a new size/style or your changes will be
                    lost.<br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>6. List of Styles</dt>
                <dd>
                    This is a list of styles for your product. Sizes have their list on their side.<br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>7. Toggle Style Selectable</dt>
                <dd>
                    Clicking this enables or disables the style(does the same thing for size). Having it enabled
                    means it is selectable in the orders dropdown menu. Disabled makes it unselectable in the orders
                    dropdown menu.<br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>8. Delete Style</dt>
                <dd>
                    This deletes the style(does the same thing for size). It is recommended that you don't delete the
                    style or the size, instead just disabling it so you won't lose any orders that are related to the
                    size or style.
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
        <br/><br/>
        <div id="manage-products">
            <h3>Manage Product</h3>
            <img src="/manage_products.png" />
            <dl>
                <dt>1. List of Products</dt>
                <dd>
                    This is a list of products that you have added in the TurkeyBase.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>2. Product Name</dt>
                <dd>
                    This is the name of a product. If you click this you will be redirected to the page to edit
                    your product.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>3. Delete Product</dt>
                <dd>
                    Click this to delete your product. It is recommended that you not delete your product. Any
                    orders that were made with the product will also be removed.
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
    </div>
