    <div id="users">
        <h2>Users</h2>
        There are 4 types of users:
        <br/><br/>
        <dl class="dl-horizontal">
            <dt>Admins</dt>
            <dd>
                Able to access the entire system. They can manage
                the orders, order seasons, products, and users. It is suggested that you only have one admin account.
            </dd>
            <dt>Login Role</dt>
            <dd>
                Login role users are your general user. These users log into your system and have the ability to
                manage your orders, including adding, editing, and deleting. They have access to no other part of
                the system.
            </dd>
            <dt>Sales</dt>
            <dd>
                Sales users don't have the ability to log in. They are the users that are available in the dropdown list when
                you are placing an <a href="#new-order">order</a>.
            </dd>
            <dt>Disabled</dt>
            <dd>
                It is recommended that you just disable a user without deleting them once you don't want them to have a role.
                This is so there is no <a href="http://database.guide/what-is-an-orphaned-record/">orphaned data</a>. If you delete
                a user, any orders that are related to that will also be deleted so no orphaned data is left.
            </dd>
        </dl>
        <br/><br/>
        <div id="new-user">
            <h3>New User</h3>
            <img src="/New_User.png"/>
            <dl>
                <dt>1. Username</dt>
                <dd>
                    The username for the user. If it's a sales user, this is what will appear in the dropdown menu in the order
                    menu.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>2. Password</dt>
                <dd>
                    The password for the user.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>3. Confirm Password</dt>
                <dd>
                    The password confirmation for the user. It must match the password
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>4. Admin Role</dt>
                <dd>
                    Check this box if the user is to be an admin. Checking this automatically checks the login role box.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>5. Login Role</dt>
                <dd>
                    Check this if the user is used to log in. Users with this role won't show up in the order menu.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>6. Save User</dt>
                <dd>
                    Save the user. If any errors are present you will be notified.
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
        <br/><br/>
        <div id="edit-user">
            <h3>Edit User</h3>
            <img src="/Edit_User.png"/>
            <dl>
                <dt>1. Username</dt>
                <dd>
                    The username for the user. If it's a sales user, this is what will appear in the dropdown menu in the order
                    menu.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>2. Password</dt>
                <dd>
                    The password for the user. If you are not changing the password, leave this field blank.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>3. Confirm Password</dt>
                <dd>
                    The password confirmation for the user. It must match the password. Leave this field blank if you are not
                    changing the password.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>4. Admin Role</dt>
                <dd>
                    Check this box if the user is to be an admin. Checking this automatically checks the login role box.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>5. Login Role</dt>
                <dd>
                    Check this if the user is used to log in. Users with this role won't show up in the order menu.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>6. Save User</dt>
                <dd>
                    Save the user. If any errors are present you will be notified.
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
        <br/><br/>
        <div id="manage-users">
            <h3>Manage Users</h3>
            <img src="/Manage_Users.png"/>
            <dl>
                <dt>1. Login Users List</dt>
                <dd>
                    A list of users who are active with the login role. These users are only used to login. They only have
                    permissions to access the management of orders.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>2. Sales Users List</dt>
                <dd>
                    A list of active users who will appear in the employee dropdown list in the new order menu.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>3. Disabled Users List</dt>
                <dd>
                    A list of disabled users. These users have no access to the system, nor do they appear in any dropdown lists.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>4. Edit User</dt>
                <dd>
                    Click this to <a href="#edit-user">edit a user</a>.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>5. Disable User</dt>
                <dd>
                    Clicking this will disable the user and send them to the disabled users list.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>6. Delete User</dt>
                <dd>
                    This is only available for disabled users. <strong>THIS ACTION IS IRRIVERSABLE!</strong>
                    It is recommended that you just leave the users disabled, otherwise deleting a user will remove any orders
                    that are related to that user.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
                <dt>7. Enable User</dt>
                <dd>
                    This re-enables the user. It moves them back to either their login role or sales role, depending on what their
                    role was before they were disabled.
                    <br/><br/>
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
    </div>
